Scotland’s independent schools continue to display academic excellence, and this has persisted in 2018 with another year of outstanding exam results, underpinned by individual and collective success in sports, arts, music and other community initiatives.
Represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools, these schools have more than 30,000 students across Scotland, working hard to deliver the very best school experience to students and parents alike.
Free schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen careers and their position as citizens of the world.
As an educational institution that can design and implement a tailored school curriculum, we see that modern languages are still a popular and sought-after elective in schools.
Nelson Mandela once said, “If you speak to a man in a language he understands, words go to his head.
If you speak to him in his own language, his words reach his heart.”
This is a powerful reminder that we can’t just stick to English when we want to build relationships and trust with people from other countries.
From this year's exam results, we see that language is at the top of the table with the highest pass rates from independent schools.
