Ri did not mention plans for a second meeting between Kim and Trump, which the US leader stressed in front of the UN earlier this week.
Instead, the minister highlighted three meetings between Kim and South Korean leader Moon Jae over the past five months, adding: “If the other party to this disarmament issue were South Korea, rather than the United States, the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula would not have been as entrenched as it is.”
