There are a few great moments in the latest Johnny English journey.
I loved how Johnny English approached a helicopter in medieval armor and the rotor blades snuffed his helmet.
Atkinson’s talent for physical comedy comes into its own, but the humor feels rather anaemic and oddly superfluous, especially now that the “serious” brands like 007 and Mission Impossible are willingly outdoing comedy.
